events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: With more distractions swirling around him, Jameis Winston was nearly flawless, throwing for 317 yards and three touchdowns, Mario Pender scored twice, and top-ranked Florida State beat Syracuse 38-20 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Winston sharp as Noles win 22nd straight

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Dak Prescott ran for two touchdowns and threw for another in leading No. 3 Mississippi State to a 38-23 victory over No. 2 Auburn on Saturday.

events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Bo Wallace ran for two scores and threw a touchdown pass, and Mississippi's defense added two scores to help the third-ranked Rebels remain undefeated with a 35-20 victory over No. 14 Texas A&M on Saturday.

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Chris Callahan kicked a 28-yard field goal as time expired, and No. 5 Baylor wiped out a 21-point deficit in the final 11 minutes to beat No. 9 TCU 61-58 on Saturday.

events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at Notre Dame Fighting Irish
